			"title": "World Drivers Championships",
			"body": "<p>The Formula One World Drivers' Championship (WDC) is the most successful Formula One race car driver of the year. The award is given by the Fédération Internationale de l'Automobile (FIA) to the driver who scores the most points during a season. The WDC was first awarded in 1950, to Giuseppe &quot;Nino&quot; Farina.</p>"
